TITLE: Garlicy Pickled Tomatoes

DESCRIPTION: An easy way to make tomatoes taste amazing. These tomatoes serve as a great topping for sandwiches, salads, and toast.

PREP: 10 minutes
COOK: 10 minutes + at least 24 hours to pickle
YIELD: 1 pint
IMAGE: pickled-tomatoes.jpg

INGREDIENTS:
1 pint cherry tomatoes, washed
4 cloves of garlic, sliced
1 tsp dried oregano
1 tsp whole peppercorns
2-3 dried red chilis (optional)
-- Brine
1 cup water
1/2 cup apple cider vinegar
2 tsp sugar
1 tsp salt


DIRECTIONS:
Halve tomatoes and place in a 1 quart jar, along with garlic, oregano, and peppercorns.
In a small pot, heat brine ingredients until boiling, then reduce heat and simmer for five minutes.
Laddle hot brine into jar with tomatoes. Leave jar open and allow to cool to room temperature.
Refridgerate for at least 24 hours.

